generated_solutions.gemini-1.5-flash: Let $P$ be the perimeter of one of the congruent rectangles.  Since the large rectangle is divided into five congruent rectangles, the perimeter of the large rectangle is $5P$.  We are given that the perimeter of the large rectangle is 176, so $5P=176$.  Dividing both sides by 5, we find $P=\boxed{35.2}$.
